

workflow

remote repo -> working directort -> staging/index area -> local repository

git tracks files only on staging

git save credentials
==========================================================================


git clone < remote_repo_url>  # only once

edit/add file in local repo

git add .
git add --all
git add <file_name>

git commit -m <commit_message>
git commit -a -m <commit_message>  # add to stage and commit at a timre

git pull

git push


# to move file from staged to working directory

git restore --staged <file_name>

git restore <file_name> # remove file from working dir

# to configure username and email

git configure --name



====================================

git log
git log â€“oneline
git log -2 # gives latest 2 commits
git log --pretty=%h

====================================
# show all details of commit id
git show <commit_id>
git show --name-only <commit_id>

====================================

to undo

# Revert and Reset

git revert <commit id>  #this will create new commit upon commit id mentioned, keeping existance commit safe


git reset  --hard <commit_id> # whatever commit above this commit id , it ill be removed
git push --force
=======================================
12-02-2024

-> if readme file is not created while creating remote repo , then branch will not be created (1st commit)
-> if readme option is not created while creating remote repo, then we should manually create , then commit
-> branch is created only after 1st commit.

git branch  # to list branch.

git branch <branch_name> # to create a branch

--------------------

default branch - Master 

git push --all # to push changes from all branch
git remote -v # details about origin
git push origin
git push origin <new_branch>

-------------
# to switch between other branches

git checkout <other_branch>
